set_preemption

public void set_preemption(java.lang.String preemption)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
 Enable or disable the preemption of a cluster node that is configured as SPARE by a node that is configured as ACTIVE. When preemption is enabled, ACTIVE nodes are given precedence over SPARE nodes. This means that when an ACTIVE node comes online and finds that a SPARE node is serving traffic, it preempts the SPARE node and starts serving traffic. When preemption is disabled, the SPARE node continues serving traffic even after an ACTIVE node comes back online.
 Default value: DISABLED
 Possible values = ENABLED, DISABLED

Throws:
java.lang.Exception

get_preemption

public java.lang.String get_preemption()
                                throws java.lang.Exception
 Enable or disable the preemption of a cluster node that is configured as SPARE by a node that is configured as ACTIVE. When preemption is enabled, ACTIVE nodes are given precedence over SPARE nodes. This means that when an ACTIVE node comes online and finds that a SPARE node is serving traffic, it preempts the SPARE node and starts serving traffic. When preemption is disabled, the SPARE node continues serving traffic even after an ACTIVE node comes back online.
 Default value: DISABLED
